Use this folder for any sMD simulations. They continue from the last equilibration.
Depending on your system, you may need to restrain the areas you will eventually pull in the heat and equilibration phases.
Refer to the AMBER manual for more information.

To easily get resid restraints in VMD's tk console:

Load in the strip file, as well as any .nc file.

set my_frags {<space separated list of desired fragments to restrain>}

set sel [atomselect top "fragment $my_frags"]

set res_list [lsort -unique -integer [$sel get resid]]

set amber_mask [join $res_list ","]

puts "Your AMBER mask selection should be:"
puts ":$amber_mask"

Then, condense into dashed sections in a comma seperated list, with @CA if fragments are proteins or &!@H if lipids.
